Prep the ingredients: Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of salted
water to a boil. Meanwhile, halve the @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise and cut into
1/2-inch pieces). Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely
chopped). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the
@ground beef{8%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for about
~{6%minutes}, breaking up the pieces, until no longer pink.

Cook the vegetables: Add the onions and zucchini and season with salt and pepper.
Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the garlic and
@Italian seasoning{1%teaspoon} and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Add the @crushed tomatoes{1%box}, @water{1/2%cup}, and the
@chili flakes{1%teaspoon}(to taste) to the pan. Simmer for about ~{10%minutes},
until thickened.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for
~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente. Drain and add to the pan with the sauce. Toss
to combine.

Finish: Serve the tomato-garlic ragu in bowls with a sprinkle of
@Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} on top!